Here is another Indian family web series entertainer with lots of nostalgia. It connects every Indian kid's heart, especially if the kid is from before the smartphone era.

Yes, the title is "#90's A Middle Class Biopic", but it's nothing to do with 90's time.

It reminds your parents, siblings, school, friends, teachers, childhood family dinners, exams, marksheets and it reminds you of the real YOU.

Congratulations to the makers, actors and crew. A special congratulations to the director #AdityaHasan. Good job brother.

The original language of the film is in Telugu, if you cannot follow the story, closed captions will help.

But it’s a must watch show.

https://www.imdb.com/title/tt29764006/

Just watched Indian Telugu-language superhero film HANUMAN. 
A best socio mythological plot after decades in Indian cinema.
Uplifting VFX for the best story, not the story for VFX.
Quality does matter, not the quantity.
Topper than all so called PAN Indian movies, so far.
Congratulations to the makers, your hardwork is paid now.
Finally the writer and director Prashanth Varma is the HANUMan OF THE SHOW
